==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hale
<hw>Hale</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>hail</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[OE. <ets>heil</ets>, Icel.
<ets>heill</ets>; akin to E. <ets>whole</ets>. See
<er>Whole</er>.]</ety> <def>Sound; entire; healthy; robust; not
impaired; <as>as, a <ex>hale</ex> body</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Last year we thought him strong and <qex>hale</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hale</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hale
<hw>Hale</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Welfare.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All heedless of his dearest <qex>hale</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hale</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Hale
<hw>Hale</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧l ⟦or⟧ h⟦add⟧l; 277)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Haled</conjf> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧ld
<it>or</it> h⟦add⟧ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Haling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>halen</ets>,
<ets>halien</ets>; cf. AS. <ets>holian</ets>, to acquire, get. See
<er>Haul</er>.]</ety> <def>To pull; to drag; to haul.</def> See
<er>Haul</er>. <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Easier both to freight, and to <qex>hale</qex> ashore.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As some dark priest <qex>hales</qex> the reluctant victim.</q>
<rj><qau>Shelley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Halenia</ent>⟦br⟧
